<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="740" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Provisional President <persName type="from">de la
                                    Barra</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico
                                        City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-28"><hi rend="italic">May 28,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Thanking you most earnestly for your friendly felicitations, I send you
                            the most cordial wishes for the personal happiness of yourself, whom I
                            hold in the most sincere regard, and for the welfare of the American
                            Government and people.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">de la Barra.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>